MSNIAWH-1 04/01/2026 SS (F) SS 2026-1540 FINANCE AND
TAXATION
ORR SUBSTITUTE TO HB239
OFFERED BY SENATOR ORR
1
2
3
4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would increase the salaries of public
6 education employees.
7 Also, under existing law, there is no provision
8 for retirees and beneficiaries receiving monthly
9 benefits from the Teachers' Retirement System to
10 receive a funded longevity bonus in addition to their
11 retirement allowances.
12 This bill would provide a longevity bonus
13 payment to certain retirees and beneficiaries under the
14 Teachers' Retirement System.
15
16
17 A BILL
18 TO BE ENTITLED
19 AN ACT
20
21 Relating to the salaries of public education employees;
22 to provide for a revision of the State Minimum Salary Schedule
23 to reflect a pay increase of two percent beginning with the
24 fiscal year 2026-2027; to provide that each employee of
25 certain boards of education shall receive the pay increase
26 according to placement on the appropriate salary step; to
27 require the appropriate increases on the State Minimum Salary
28 Schedule; to provide support employees with a two percent pay
Page 1

Schedule; to provide support employees with a two percent pay
29 increase beginning with the fiscal year 2026-2027; to require
30 salary schedules; to provide the employees of certain other
31 public educational institutions and schools with a two percent
32 pay increase for the 2026-2027 fiscal year; to provide for an
33 across the board salary increase on all two-year postsecondary
34 salary schedules; to establish other requirements on the
35 two-year postsecondary salary schedules; to establish
36 miscellaneous pay provisions relating to public education; and
37 to provide for a funded one-time longevity bonus payment in
38 addition to the retirement benefits of certain retirees and
39 beneficiaries of the Teachers' Retirement System.
40 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
41 Section 1. PAY INCREASES, FY 2026-2027. The State
42 Budget Officer shall allocate to the State Board of Education,
43 the Board of Trustees of the Alabama Institute for Deaf and
44 Blind, the Board of Youth Services School District, the Board
45 of Directors of the Alabama School of Fine Arts, the Board of
46 Directors for the Alabama School of Cyber Technology and
47 Engineering, the Board of Trustees of the Alabama School of
48 Mathematics and Science, the Board of Trustees of the Alabama
49 School of Healthcare Sciences and for disbursement to the
50 employees thereof funds based on the criteria established in
51 this act. It is not the intent of this act to make
52 appropriations, but the appropriations required by this act
53 shall be made in the annual Education Trust Fund budget act
54 for the designated fiscal year.
55 (1) Certificated Personnel (K-12). For the fiscal year
56 beginning October 1, 2026, and each year thereafter, each
