184 (4) Two-Year Postsecondary Institutions. The Board of
185 Trustees of the Alabama Community College System shall revise
186 all salary schedules of the two-year postsecondary
187 institutions to reflect an increase of two percent for the
188 2026-2027 fiscal year. The pay increase shall be given to each
189 person employed in addition to any step increase to which the
190 employee is otherwise entitled. The Alabama Community College
191 System shall take proper steps to ensure that employees on all
192 salary schedules are given full credit for prior work
193 experience in the public schools and colleges, and shall take
194 care to ensure proper placements on the salary schedules.
195 Placement on the revised salary schedules shall be in
196 accordance with the employee's length of service in public
Page 7

accordance with the employee's length of service in public
197 education. No pay increase shall be given to any two-year
198 postsecondary employee in excess of two percent, except as
199 specifically provided in this act.
200 (5) Miscellaneous provisions. The following provisions
201 are hereby established:
202 a. Fiscal Year. All salaries and salary increases that
203 are established by the State Board of Education shall be paid
204 in full to each person employed before the end of the
205 applicable fiscal year as defined in Section 16-1-1 of the
206 Code of Alabama 1975, as amended.
207 b. Extended Work. Public K-12 school employees on
208 contracts that extend beyond 187 days, or the hourly
209 equivalent thereof, shall be given a pro rata salary increment
210 for each or partial day of work extending beyond 187 days.
211 c. Local Increment. Any cost-of-living adjustment
212 and/or increase on the State Minimum Salary Schedule for
213 teachers as provided in this act shall be exclusive of any
214 local pay increase granted or due to teachers under provisions
215 of any local salary schedule. Any cost-of-living adjustment
216 and/or pay increase required by this act for public school
217 support personnel shall be in addition to any pay increase due
218 or granted to the employee under provisions of any local
219 salary schedules. The pay increase provisions of this act
220 shall not apply to any salary supplements granted by local
221 boards of education, bonuses earned for certification by the
222 National Board of Professional Teaching Standards, or the
223 federal portion of the salary paid to a Junior Reserve Officer
224 Training Corps (JROTC) instructor employed by a local school
Page 8

Training Corps (JROTC) instructor employed by a local school
225 board.
226 d. Community Education. Each county and city board of
227 education shall have the option to exclude from the provisions
228 of this act any part-time employees of community education or
229 school-sponsored child care or child enrichment program that
230 is supplemental to the state-required educational program.
231 e. Local Chief Executive Officers. The pay increase
232 provisions of this act shall not apply to superintendents of
233 education of any school system or institution. Any pay
234 increase given to the superintendent shall be by majority
235 recorded vote of the governing body or authority.
236 Section 2. The pay increase granted in Section 1 of
237 this act shall begin in fiscal year 2026-2027 and continue in
238 subsequent years. Nothing in this act shall authorize
239 additional pay increases in subsequent years.
240 Section 3. (a) There is provided for fiscal year
241 2026-2027 a funded one-time, lump-sum payment, hereinafter
242 referred to as "longevity bonus payment," to each individual
243 whose effective date of retirement for purposes of receiving
244 benefits from the Teachers' Retirement System is prior to May
245 1, 2026, and is receiving, or is entitled to receive, a
246 monthly allowance from the Teachers' Retirement System on
247 September 30, 2026.
248 (b) The formula for calculating the longevity bonus
249 payment shall be one dollar ($1) per month for each year of
250 service attained by the retiree.
251 (c) Beneficiaries of deceased members or deceased
252 retirees, if the beneficiary is receiving or is entitled to
Page 9

retirees, if the beneficiary is receiving or is entitled to
253 receive a monthly allowance from the Teachers' Retirement
254 System on September 30, 2026, shall receive a longevity bonus
255 payment of one dollar ($1) per month for each year of service
256 of the deceased member or deceased retiree.
257 (d) For purposes of this section, service includes the
258 service under Section 16-25-1 and Article 9, commencing with
259 Section 16-25-150, Chapter 25, Title 16, Code of Alabama 1975.
260 (e) Any individual who received benefits under the
261 Medicaid program, and whose eligibility for Medicaid benefits
262 would be impaired by the longevity bonus payment provided by
263 this section, shall not be entitled to receive the
264 aforementioned increase. Any individual who subsequently
265 applies for benefits under the Medicaid program, and that
266 individual's eligibility to receive benefits is impaired by
267 the longevity bonus payment provided by this section, shall
268 not be entitled to receive the increase subsequent to the date
269 that the member files application for benefits under the
270 Medicaid program.
271 (f) The longevity bonus payments provided under this
272 section shall be paid to all eligible recipients by the
273 Teachers' Retirement System in October 2026.
274 (g) It is not the intent of this act to make
275 appropriations, but the amount required to pay the cost of the
276 lump-sum payments provided under Section 3 of this act shall
277 be appropriated to the Teachers' Retirement System in HB238 of
278 the 2026 Regular Session.
279 Section 4. The provisions of this act are severable. If
280 any part of this act is declared invalid or unconstitutional,
Page 10

any part of this act is declared invalid or unconstitutional,
281 that declaration shall not affect the part that remains.
282 Section 5. This act shall become effective on October
283 1, 2026.
